# Backend Conventions

## Stack

Express 4 + Prisma + PostgreSQL (Neon). Logger: Bunyan.

## Routes (under `/api/v1`)

| File | Domain |
|------|--------|
| `routes/auth.route.js` | Google OAuth, refresh tokens |
| `routes/event.route.js` | Event CRUD, registration, teams, tickets, checkin, stats, PDF reports |
| `routes/user.route.js` | Profile |
| `routes/council.route.js` | Council members |
| `routes/document.route.js` | Event documents |
| `routes/budget.route.js` | Event budget items |
| `routes/announcement.route.js` | Announcements |
| `routes/mailer.route.js` | Email (via `utils/mailer.js` + `utils/email-template.js`) |

Protected event routes use prefix `/event/p/` + `authCheck` middleware.

## Event update rules

`validateUpdateFields` strips forbidden fields by role. Notable:

- `state`, `comment` — FACULTY, PRINCIPAL, COUNCIL (state); comment writers: FACULTY, PRINCIPAL
- `state_history` — auto-appended on state change in update handler, not client-writable

On state change in `event.route.js`:

- Return to `DRAFT` requires non-empty `comment`
- Approve/forward clears `comment`
- Council resubmit (`DRAFT` → `APPLIED_FOR_APPROVAL`) clears `comment`
- Faculty: `APPLIED_FOR_APPROVAL` → `UNLISTED` | `APPLIED_FOR_PRINCI_APPROVAL` | `DRAFT`
- Principal: `APPLIED_FOR_PRINCI_APPROVAL` → `UNLISTED` | `DRAFT`

## Prisma

- Schema: `backend/prisma/schema.prisma`
- Client singleton: `backend/utils/prisma_client.js`
- Run migrations from `backend/` directory

## Patterns

- Use existing `logger.error` for failures
- Invalidate event cache via `invalidateEvent()` after mutations
- Role checks at route level before Prisma calls

## Email

- **Single entry point:** `utils/mailer.js` — do not call nodemailer from routes
- **Layout:** `utils/email-template.js` (`buildEventioEmail`, `buildAnnouncementEmail`, `buildTeamInviteEmail`)
- Helpers: `sendAnnouncementEmail`, `sendTeamInviteEmail`, `sendGenericEmail`
- Legacy `/mailer/send-email` auto-wraps plain `body`/`html` unless already an Eventio template
